# Zod Validation Patterns (Backend)

This project uses **Zod v4**. The v4 API differs from v3 — do not copy v3 patterns.

## Defining Schemas

Schemas live in `src/schemas/`. One file per domain (e.g. `todoSchemas.ts`).

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — Zod v4 schema with inferred type
import { z } from 'zod';

export const createTodoSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1, 'Title is required').max(255),
  completed: z.boolean().optional().default(false),
});

export type CreateTodoInput = z.infer<typeof createTodoSchema>;
```

## Parsing in Controllers

Always use **`safeParse`** in controllers — never `parse` (throws untyped).

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — throws untyped ZodError, not caught by errorHandler correctly
const data = createTodoSchema.parse(req.body);

// ✅ GOOD — safeParse + structured error response
const result = createTodoSchema.safeParse(req.body);
if (!result.success) {
  const err = new Error('Validation failed') as Error & { statusCode: number };
  err.statusCode = 400;
  throw err;
}
const data = result.data;
```

## Rules

- **One schema per operation** (create, update may differ).
- Export both the schema and its inferred `type` from `src/schemas/`.
- Never define schemas inline inside controllers.
- Use `.optional()` + `.default()` for optional fields rather than `.nullable()` unless the DB column is genuinely nullable.
